$ VBA functions: isX()

VBA offers a few functions whose names start with `is…()` to test if a variable has a certain type or characteristic. These functions are especially useful when dealing with
→ development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes/variant[variants].

These functsions are
table { ll

    `isArray` ☰
    `isDate` ☰
    `isEmpty` ☰ Test if a → development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes/variant is → development/languages/VBA/language/null-and-nothing-etc#vba-empty[`empty`]
    `isError` ☰
    `isNumeric` ☰
    `isMissing` ☰ Check if an → development/languages/VBA/language/subs-and-functions/optional-parameters[optional parameter] was assigned a value when the → development/languages/VBA/language/subs-and-functions[sub/function] was invoked. See → development/languages/VBA/language/subs-and-functions/optional-parameters/keyword-isMissing[here]
    `isNull` ☰ Test if a → development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes/variant is → development/languages/VBA/language/null-and-nothing-etc#vba-null[`null`].
    `isObject` ☰
table }


